{htxt id='label-tokens'}
<p>{ts}The following tokens are available to format Mailing Labels. Address fields are taken from the contact's <strong>primary</strong> location.{/ts}</p>
<div class="form-item">
<table style="">
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{contact_name}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Used for mailing labels only. Replaced by the configurable Individual Name format for individuals and the display name for Organizations and Households.{/ts}</td></tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{street_address}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Full street address (e.g. 110 Main Street).{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{supplemental_address_1}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Supplemental address 1 (line is skipped if empty).{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{supplemental_address_2}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Supplemental address 2 (line is skipped if empty).{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{city}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}City.{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{county}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}County name. If you want to include the county in your mailing labels, the <strong>Include Counties</strong> setting must be enabled on this screen, and county names must be added to the civicrm_county table in your database.{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{state_province}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}State or province <strong>abbreviation</strong>.{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{state_province_name}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}State or province <strong>full name</strong>.{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{postal_code}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Postal code.{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{country}{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Country name (e.g. Canada).{/ts}</td>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td style="padding-right:1em;">{literal}{, }{/literal}</td><td>{ts}Add spaces or punctuation to layout by surrounding them with brackets.{/ts}</td>
</table>
</div>
{/htxt}
